found.>org.xml.sax.SAXParseException: Document is invalid: no grammar found.

Apparently because I removed the DOCTYPE which according to tomcat documentation is not required to be in the web.xml file.   

I don't understand why your system is so much more "picky" then mine.  
I will look at it more and I will install 3.2.2 and see if that is what causes the pickiness.

Apparently there is a new constraint on the order of the Servlet and servlet-mapping statements on the web.xml file.
puttin all the servlet-mapping statements after all the servlet statements fixed the problem.  
One additional note.  Although I could not reproduce the exception, I did find that using the xml editor in eclipse did show the error.  
I could find no documentation for the servlet servlet-papping order but if that is what they want so be it.
Nelson has verified that the exception is gone.
